The mutual opposition of the two clauses under ‘ut’ is expressed by the emphatic ‘tu sis‚’ ‘ non ego si1n,' ‘you are, 1 am not.' ‘ Habeat ¹ is potential. We are still feeling the hypo- thetieal construction of ‘ut sis,' etc. ‘It does not follow that my writing should lie in any bookseller’s shop.’ To make it optative renders the transition to ‘ nec recito’ impossible, as Bentley felt. You can pass from a modified statement to an unmodified one, but a wish and a fact cannot be connected by ‘ nec.'
